cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with optimizing the allocation of computational resources in a cloud data center. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of server allocation policies on network traffic and user experience. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a control policy for dynamically powering servers on and off to minimize electricity consumption. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve software engineering techniques for implementing the proposed allocation policies. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also less likely but possible as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed scheme under different traffic conditions.
